1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,280
Characters, actions, places, occupations,

2
00:00:04,280 --> 00:00:09,240
and events in this series are fictional and created for entertainment purposes only.

3
00:00:09,240 --> 00:00:16,400
They are not intended to urge or promote any behavior in the series.

4
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:18,800
I won’t change my mind. I won’t do it.

5
00:00:19,040 --> 00:00:21,240
I’m trying to find solutions for you.

6
00:00:21,560 --> 00:00:22,720
Can you try to work with me?

7
00:00:23,040 --> 00:00:27,240
But you know that Bambi broke up with me
because of work before.

8
00:00:27,520 --> 00:00:30,800
Shasha will be working in the business
for several years.

9
00:00:31,080 --> 00:00:34,280
I don’t want you to go public
with your relationship.

10
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:36,160
It’s alright.

11
00:00:36,400 --> 00:00:38,560
She wants to spend time
with her girlfriend.

12
00:00:38,920 --> 00:00:40,440
You will get new projects.

13
00:00:40,880 --> 00:00:42,360
Let them take some rest.

14
00:00:42,720 --> 00:00:45,640
Sometimes, you need to be selfish.

15
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:48,080
Don’t love me more than yourself.

16
00:00:48,120 --> 00:00:48,960
Do you get it?

17
00:00:49,240 --> 00:00:50,840
I got past that point.

18
00:00:51,400 --> 00:00:53,760
Now I know what I need to do
to balance things in my life.

19
00:00:54,120 --> 00:00:57,240
Or should I disappear from her life?

20
00:00:57,640 --> 00:00:59,280
So she will have a better life.

21
00:01:02,240 --> 00:01:04,160
Did you cancel all schedules
for this month?

22
00:01:08,160 --> 00:01:09,160
It’s because you are busy.

23
00:01:09,400 --> 00:01:11,640
I can’t answer our clients
when you will be available to work.

24
00:01:11,720 --> 00:01:12,920
So I have to cancel all schedules.

25
00:01:13,120 --> 00:01:14,480
Why didn’t you ask me first?

26
00:01:14,560 --> 00:01:15,680
You can ask me for each schedule.

27
00:01:15,680 --> 00:01:18,360
If I’m not available on that schedule,
then you find another director.

28
00:01:18,440 --> 00:01:20,120
Who should I hire to replace you?

29
00:01:20,240 --> 00:01:22,960
The clients come to us
because they like your work.

30
00:01:23,480 --> 00:01:25,560
When you are not available,
they don’t hire us.

31
00:01:25,600 --> 00:01:27,720
But you should have a better solution
to handle the situation.

32
00:01:27,760 --> 00:01:28,880
I tried.

33
00:01:29,320 --> 00:01:31,280
I went to apologize to our clients.

34
00:01:31,680 --> 00:01:33,360
I had to come up with an excuse.

35
00:01:33,759 --> 00:01:36,840
Because I couldn’t tell them that
you refused to work on the Phuket project

36
00:01:36,960 --> 00:01:38,360
because you wanted to take care of Bambi.

37
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:41,600
Everyone has personal things to do.

38
00:01:41,759 --> 00:01:43,160
Do you think I don’t have ones?

39
00:01:44,200 --> 00:01:46,160
I want to have my personal time too.

40
00:01:46,640 --> 00:01:48,840
But I have to be here to cover for you.

41
00:01:50,039 --> 00:01:50,960
I’m tired.

42
00:01:51,560 --> 00:01:54,960
The love that you sacrifice your work for,
I hope it's worth it.

43
00:01:55,640 --> 00:01:57,080
Don’t call me.

44
00:01:57,479 --> 00:01:59,360
Don’t come to cry with me.

45
00:02:02,200 --> 00:02:03,960
I won’t be your doormat anymore.

46
00:02:08,199 --> 00:02:09,680
If I make a wrong choice,

47
00:02:11,120 --> 00:02:12,840
I’ll take responsibility for it.

48
00:02:13,400 --> 00:02:14,760
I’ll cry alone.

49
00:02:14,880 --> 00:02:16,440
You don’t need to comfort me.

50
00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:18,640
If you are tired,

51
00:02:19,040 --> 00:02:20,160
you can stop.

52
00:02:25,480 --> 00:02:26,360
Fine.

53
00:02:27,720 --> 00:02:28,840
I’ll stop.

54
00:02:30,880 --> 00:02:32,360
I’ll withdraw from the company.

55
00:02:33,480 --> 00:02:35,640
You need to find a new producer.

56
00:03:38,880 --> 00:03:39,680
Wow.

57
00:03:40,160 --> 00:03:42,160
You look so cool.

58
00:03:42,440 --> 00:03:44,160
You can play a spy with this look.

59
00:03:44,680 --> 00:03:45,760
You’re overstating.

60
00:03:45,920 --> 00:03:47,040
I like it.

61
00:03:47,079 --> 00:03:48,760
Normally, I don’t wear
this style of clothes.

62
00:03:49,040 --> 00:03:50,480
You look beautiful and cool.

63
00:03:50,520 --> 00:03:51,880
This is what the client wants.

64
00:03:52,400 --> 00:03:53,280
Right.

65
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:54,920
I feel confident now.

66
00:03:55,040 --> 00:03:59,640
A compliment from my girlfriend
makes me look a hundred times better.

67
00:03:59,760 --> 00:04:00,560
Don’t overstate it.

68
00:04:00,960 --> 00:04:02,640
You are cast in an international film.

69
00:04:02,640 --> 00:04:04,760
Will you dump me
if you become more famous?

70
00:04:04,920 --> 00:04:06,040
Why would I dump you?

71
00:04:06,080 --> 00:04:07,320
I told you.

72
00:04:07,360 --> 00:04:10,440
You would be by my side
in both my work and personal life.

73
00:04:11,480 --> 00:04:15,080
Who knows? Fame can change people.

74
00:04:17,399 --> 00:04:18,560
Don’t worry.

75
00:04:20,279 --> 00:04:23,480
I told you that if I could choose,
I wouldn’t choose this career.

76
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:25,360
I would choose to have a girlfriend

77
00:04:25,880 --> 00:04:27,240
and cuddle her.

78
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:28,680
I would kiss her.

79
00:04:28,720 --> 00:04:29,320
No.

80
00:04:29,320 --> 00:04:31,080
Shasha, you will ruin your makeup.

81
00:04:31,960 --> 00:04:33,080
Don’t you like it?

82
00:04:33,240 --> 00:04:34,200
Stop, you will ruin your makeup.

83
00:04:34,200 --> 00:04:35,760
-Shasha.
-Can I…

84
00:04:37,440 --> 00:04:38,760
Why are you wearing that?

85
00:04:39,520 --> 00:04:42,520
This event is full of
famous directors and producers.

86
00:04:42,840 --> 00:04:44,760
Why don’t you wear a better outfit?

87
00:04:45,520 --> 00:04:47,280
This is the style I usually wear.

88
00:04:47,320 --> 00:04:48,440
I like it.

89
00:04:49,400 --> 00:04:52,000
It’s because your stylist only arranges
this style of outfit for you.

90
00:04:52,200 --> 00:04:53,440
You are beautiful.

91
00:04:53,480 --> 00:04:55,360
You should present your feminine beauty.

92
00:04:56,200 --> 00:04:59,640
Sha’s character in her next movie
has cool looks.

93
00:04:59,880 --> 00:05:01,920
Moreover, this is the look
the client requests.

94
00:05:02,200 --> 00:05:03,040
It’s okay.

95
00:05:03,320 --> 00:05:05,040
This is a big event.

96
00:05:05,120 --> 00:05:07,360
I want to see Sha in a different style.

97
00:05:07,920 --> 00:05:10,040
She’s going to meet new directors.

98
00:05:10,440 --> 00:05:12,760
I want her to show
that she has various looks.

99
00:05:13,600 --> 00:05:16,160
Look at your outfit.

100
00:05:16,200 --> 00:05:17,480
It doesn’t make you shine.

101
00:05:17,520 --> 00:05:19,080
Others will get all the attention.

102
00:05:20,280 --> 00:05:21,920
Did you do your homework?

103
00:05:22,560 --> 00:05:24,480
Did you see the guest list?

104
00:05:24,920 --> 00:05:26,560
Big names are attending the event.

105
00:05:26,600 --> 00:05:28,840
And this is what you want her to wear?

106
00:05:29,480 --> 00:05:30,800
I did my homework.

107
00:05:31,240 --> 00:05:32,840
Before you stepped in,

108
00:05:32,880 --> 00:05:34,440
I had already
discussed everything with her.

109
00:05:34,640 --> 00:05:36,360
The client also approves it.

110
00:05:36,560 --> 00:05:38,159
But if you want to change her outfit,

111
00:05:38,720 --> 00:05:39,800
I can do that.

112
00:05:42,040 --> 00:05:43,840
From now on,

113
00:05:43,880 --> 00:05:47,640
please send me photos of the outfit
she will wear for every event.

114
00:05:47,720 --> 00:05:49,080
So there won’t be any mistakes.

115
00:05:50,080 --> 00:05:51,240
For today’s event,

116
00:05:51,480 --> 00:05:54,840
I think she should wear
an outfit with a feminine vibe.

117
00:05:55,320 --> 00:05:57,159
So people will see you as an actress.

118
00:05:59,120 --> 00:06:01,360
An actress doesn’t always
need to look feminine.

119
00:06:03,080 --> 00:06:05,840
But this is what I want.

120
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:14,920
Gorya did her job well
in choosing this outfit.

121
00:06:14,960 --> 00:06:16,800
This is what I chose to wear.

122
00:06:18,040 --> 00:06:20,160
But you can still change your mind.

123
00:06:21,200 --> 00:06:22,360
Here.

124
00:06:23,160 --> 00:06:24,560
I prepared a dress for you.

125
00:06:25,200 --> 00:06:27,560
This is my staff.

126
00:06:29,360 --> 00:06:31,400
I already have Gorya to do the job.

127
00:06:32,880 --> 00:06:34,760
Sha, your schedule is hectic.

128
00:06:34,880 --> 00:06:36,840
You need more staff.

129
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:39,120
You need professionals to help you.

130
00:06:46,080 --> 00:06:47,440
Are you really leaving Prim?

131
00:06:49,280 --> 00:06:50,560
She won’t care.

132
00:06:51,120 --> 00:06:52,440
Has she ever cared about anyone?

133
00:06:52,720 --> 00:06:54,840
All she cares about is Bambi.

134
00:06:58,240 --> 00:06:59,600
I think she cares about you.

135
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:02,560
But she’s probably afraid
to lose her love.

136
00:07:03,240 --> 00:07:04,760
That’s how life is.

137
00:07:05,360 --> 00:07:07,040
No one gets everything.

138
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:10,640
What if this happened to us?

139
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:15,240
What if I really needed you,
but you had to choose work before me?

140
00:07:16,280 --> 00:07:17,720
I think I would understand you,

141
00:07:18,720 --> 00:07:20,040
but it would still hurt.

142
00:07:27,640 --> 00:07:28,440
Min.

143
00:07:29,600 --> 00:07:33,080
Why don’t you set aside your roles
as her business partner and producer,

144
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:35,960
and just be her friend?

145
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:39,560
Maybe it will help you understand her.

146
00:07:46,480 --> 00:07:48,159
I have so many problems to deal with.

147
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:53,480
Luckily, there’s no problem between us.

148
00:07:55,080 --> 00:07:55,960
Yes, we do.

149
00:07:57,320 --> 00:07:58,480
What problem do we have?

150
00:08:02,600 --> 00:08:04,760
I want you to come
and hang out with my friends.

151
00:08:05,560 --> 00:08:07,480
I want you to meet my circle of friends.

152
00:08:07,800 --> 00:08:09,160
I want to show you off to them.

153
00:08:11,640 --> 00:08:12,560
Sure.

154
00:08:13,720 --> 00:08:15,240
But I need to visit my mom first.

155
00:08:15,280 --> 00:08:16,240
I’ll meet you there.

156
00:08:24,160 --> 00:08:25,680
Don’t stress about it.

157
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:31,320
Thank you. You are the only thing
that makes me smile.

158
00:08:44,159 --> 00:08:44,960
Ginny.

159
00:08:45,200 --> 00:08:46,440
Bambi.

160
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:50,880
Ginny, this is Prim.

161
00:08:52,320 --> 00:08:54,080
Prim wants to make a movie.

162
00:08:54,520 --> 00:08:56,760
She has been writing movie scripts
since she was in college.

163
00:08:56,760 --> 00:08:58,800
Prim, why don’t you
send your scripts to her?

164
00:08:58,840 --> 00:09:01,040
Ginny has produced many hit movies.

165
00:09:01,560 --> 00:09:03,240
I’ve known her for a while.

166
00:09:03,920 --> 00:09:06,280
Many of my favorite movies
are produced by her.

167
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:08,840
Why don’t you send your script to me?

168
00:09:09,200 --> 00:09:11,640
I’m searching for new directors.

169
00:09:12,160 --> 00:09:14,480
Bambi told me a lot about you.

170
00:09:14,960 --> 00:09:16,840
Why don’t you come to my office
so we can talk?

171
00:09:17,600 --> 00:09:20,280
Sure, I’ll send my script to you.

172
00:09:20,480 --> 00:09:22,200
Excuse me. I’ll go inside first.

173
00:09:26,800 --> 00:09:31,120
If I get to work with her on a movie,
it will be my dream come true.

174
00:09:31,440 --> 00:09:32,880
You can do it.

175
00:09:33,160 --> 00:09:35,520
You will achieve your dream
of being a film director.

176
00:09:35,560 --> 00:09:37,680
Tell Min to have your account ready.

177
00:09:37,680 --> 00:09:40,400
Your company will make millions from it.

178
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:49,880
Have you not reconciled with Min?

179
00:09:50,920 --> 00:09:51,680
No.

180
00:09:54,120 --> 00:09:55,880
We are fighting over trivial things.

181
00:09:56,840 --> 00:09:59,080
This is how it is
when you open a business with your friend.

182
00:10:00,440 --> 00:10:01,960
She resigned from the company.

183
00:10:02,480 --> 00:10:03,680
Is it that bad?

184
00:10:07,400 --> 00:10:08,960
It’s okay. Don’t worry about it.

185
00:10:12,880 --> 00:10:15,160
I still have you.

186
00:10:16,120 --> 00:10:18,960
Everything will get better.

187
00:10:21,840 --> 00:10:23,160
I want to thank you.

188
00:10:24,120 --> 00:10:26,040
You helped me find my goal in life.

189
00:10:28,520 --> 00:10:29,480
Don’t overthink it.

190
00:10:29,480 --> 00:10:31,160
Come on. Let’s go inside.

191
00:10:31,480 --> 00:10:33,480
They will announce the lineup soon.
I want to see it.

192
00:10:39,840 --> 00:10:40,640
I’m sorry.

193
00:10:40,880 --> 00:10:41,840
-I didn’t mean it.
-It’s okay.

194
00:10:41,880 --> 00:10:43,200
It’s okay.

195
00:10:43,240 --> 00:10:45,440
Bambi, your dress is ripped.

196
00:10:45,440 --> 00:10:46,960
It’s okay. You should go in first.

197
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:48,720
I reserved a seat next to Ginny for you.

198
00:10:48,720 --> 00:10:49,520
Are you sure?

199
00:10:49,560 --> 00:10:50,800
Yes, I can fix my dress. Don’t worry.

200
00:10:50,800 --> 00:10:51,640
It’s okay.

201
00:10:51,640 --> 00:10:53,760
Hurry up. Go inside.

202
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:37,600
Shasha is here.

203
00:11:37,760 --> 00:11:39,040
Shasha.

204
00:11:39,080 --> 00:11:40,440
Hello.

205
00:11:41,720 --> 00:11:43,040
Please look at this camera.

206
00:11:43,360 --> 00:11:45,080
Please look this way.

207
00:11:45,080 --> 00:11:46,960
This is a new look for you.

208
00:11:48,920 --> 00:11:50,280
You look great.

209
00:11:52,240 --> 00:11:53,080
See?

210
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:56,720
I think this outfit is perfect for Sha.

211
00:11:57,360 --> 00:11:58,680
She looks like an international star.

212
00:11:59,640 --> 00:12:02,480
Yes, she looks great.

213
00:12:03,600 --> 00:12:05,960
But she doesn’t look
confident in the outfit.

214
00:12:07,040 --> 00:12:10,040
Sha doesn’t know what is good for her.

215
00:12:10,360 --> 00:12:11,640
I have to choose it for her.

216
00:12:13,800 --> 00:12:15,240
Can you flip your hair?

217
00:12:15,320 --> 00:12:16,080
Sure.

218
00:12:24,840 --> 00:12:25,960
You don’t need to step in.

219
00:12:26,360 --> 00:12:28,160
My staff will take care of it.

220
00:12:28,520 --> 00:12:29,640
I hired them for this.

221
00:12:36,480 --> 00:12:38,960
But it’s my job to take care of her.

222
00:12:40,520 --> 00:12:41,560
It’s okay.

223
00:12:41,640 --> 00:12:43,160
This is a big event.

224
00:12:43,400 --> 00:12:45,440
You should let someone
with experience do it.

225
00:12:46,960 --> 00:12:47,760
One more thing,

226
00:12:48,200 --> 00:12:51,200
I already asked you to keep your distance.

227
00:12:51,240 --> 00:12:52,760
People might gossip about you two.

228
00:12:53,400 --> 00:12:54,560
Gossip about what?

229
00:12:54,960 --> 00:12:56,080
I’m her stylist.

230
00:12:57,160 --> 00:12:58,680
People can gossip about anything.

231
00:12:59,320 --> 00:13:00,560
I want to be cautious.

232
00:13:18,640 --> 00:13:20,360
Bambi, I didn’t know you also came.

233
00:13:20,560 --> 00:13:21,560
Where is Prim?

234
00:13:24,480 --> 00:13:26,040
Prim went inside first.

235
00:13:28,880 --> 00:13:29,760
What’s wrong?

236
00:13:34,240 --> 00:13:36,040
What happened to your dress?

237
00:13:48,200 --> 00:13:48,880
Hey.

238
00:13:50,160 --> 00:13:51,160
What’s wrong?

239
00:13:51,480 --> 00:13:53,880
Is it because your dress is ripped?

240
00:13:54,120 --> 00:13:56,560
I’m not crying because of that.

241
00:14:20,040 --> 00:14:21,960
I’m tired, Gorya?

242
00:14:25,520 --> 00:14:27,560
I have an amazing girlfriend.

243
00:14:30,720 --> 00:14:32,480
But why am I not happy?

244
00:14:34,960 --> 00:14:36,080
Do you know

245
00:14:36,840 --> 00:14:38,760
that Prim and Min are fighting?

246
00:14:43,440 --> 00:14:44,880
It’s because of me.

247
00:14:46,880 --> 00:14:49,680
I’m ruining their company.

248
00:14:53,280 --> 00:14:54,440
Are you sure?

249
00:14:56,840 --> 00:14:57,960
I don’t think so.

250
00:15:02,480 --> 00:15:03,880
They are friends.

251
00:15:04,160 --> 00:15:05,760
I’m sure they will work things out.

252
00:15:08,880 --> 00:15:11,960
Prim has to choose between me, her work,

253
00:15:13,080 --> 00:15:14,280
and her friend.

254
00:15:14,720 --> 00:15:16,440
Is this how it’s going to be?

255
00:15:29,040 --> 00:15:30,280
You know what?

256
00:15:37,920 --> 00:15:40,280
My bucket list.

257
00:15:53,920 --> 00:15:56,600
All I want is to see Prim’s success.

258
00:16:04,520 --> 00:16:07,440
Today, I introduced her to a producer.

259
00:16:12,760 --> 00:16:15,240
One day, she will have a chance
to make her movie.

260
00:16:25,200 --> 00:16:27,240
Then she will win an award.

261
00:16:33,560 --> 00:16:35,280
If I’m still with her,

262
00:16:38,440 --> 00:16:40,880
she might never achieve her dream.

263
00:16:44,560 --> 00:16:45,360
Bambi.

264
00:16:45,920 --> 00:16:46,960
Listen.

265
00:16:47,520 --> 00:16:51,160
I think Prim would want you
to be next to her

266
00:16:51,560 --> 00:16:53,640
when she becomes successful.

267
00:17:08,040 --> 00:17:09,240
Thank you.

268
00:17:12,359 --> 00:17:15,240
You said you wanted to be my friend.

269
00:17:18,240 --> 00:17:19,359
I am now your friend.

270
00:17:30,960 --> 00:17:31,800
So?

271
00:17:37,640 --> 00:17:39,560
How are things between you and Shasha?

272
00:17:39,760 --> 00:17:41,360
I heard that her mom is back.

273
00:17:43,040 --> 00:17:44,760
Yes, she’s back.

274
00:17:45,240 --> 00:17:46,960
I’m not sure if she is an angel

275
00:17:48,520 --> 00:17:49,560
or a devil.

276
00:17:51,600 --> 00:17:52,880
Whatever she is,

277
00:17:52,920 --> 00:17:54,560
I’m sure you can handle her.

278
00:17:56,320 --> 00:17:58,760
If you were not dating Shasha,

279
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:01,560
I would set you up with Prim.

280
00:18:03,080 --> 00:18:04,040
No.

281
00:18:04,200 --> 00:18:05,640
I’m completely over her.

282
00:18:08,440 --> 00:18:11,640
You are a perfect match for Prim.

283
00:18:13,440 --> 00:18:14,960
Don’t leave her.

284
00:18:33,040 --> 00:18:35,640
We finally graduated.

285
00:18:39,920 --> 00:18:41,360
Bottoms up.

286
00:18:43,280 --> 00:18:44,280
She’s tough.

287
00:18:46,480 --> 00:18:49,280
You don’t need to finish the whole glass.

288
00:18:49,680 --> 00:18:51,480
These guys are heavyweights.

289
00:18:52,400 --> 00:18:55,560
I’ve had my wild days before I grew up.

290
00:18:59,320 --> 00:19:01,320
Are you an owner of Lady Bird?

291
00:19:02,320 --> 00:19:03,560
You mean Prim’s company?

292
00:19:03,840 --> 00:19:05,960
I heard that she will be nominated
for an award.

293
00:19:06,320 --> 00:19:07,280
Yes.

294
00:19:08,320 --> 00:19:09,240
Damn.

295
00:19:09,560 --> 00:19:10,840
That is so sick.

296
00:19:12,920 --> 00:19:14,440
How did you end up with Praew?

297
00:19:14,680 --> 00:19:16,160
You are pretty and smart.

298
00:19:16,160 --> 00:19:17,000
Right, guys?

299
00:19:17,040 --> 00:19:17,880
Yes.

300
00:19:17,920 --> 00:19:19,720
Hey, aren’t you my friends?

301
00:19:19,760 --> 00:19:20,840
Are you supposed to be on my side?

302
00:19:21,800 --> 00:19:24,280
I want to know
why you are dating a kid like her.

303
00:19:25,560 --> 00:19:29,640
She makes me feel comfortable and smile.

304
00:19:29,720 --> 00:19:31,560
She opens a door to a new world for me.

305
00:19:32,360 --> 00:19:33,640
Isn’t that enough?

306
00:19:34,320 --> 00:19:36,680
She’s also pretty and cute.

307
00:19:40,400 --> 00:19:45,240
I want to know who is prettier,
your ex or Praew?

308
00:19:49,280 --> 00:19:50,880
Stop asking nonsense questions.

309
00:19:51,120 --> 00:19:53,280
Don’t you see
you’re making her feel uncomfortable?

310
00:19:53,520 --> 00:19:55,080
It’s okay. You can ask me.

311
00:19:55,520 --> 00:19:57,040
Of course, Praew is prettier.

312
00:19:57,440 --> 00:20:00,000
Because my ex is a guy.

313
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:09,240
She just switched teams.

314
00:20:10,600 --> 00:20:12,560
So you are bi?

315
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:14,480
Or you are non-binary?

316
00:20:16,480 --> 00:20:18,280
I’ve never thought about that before.

317
00:20:18,480 --> 00:20:19,560
What is the difference?

318
00:20:19,840 --> 00:20:22,080
If you are bi,

319
00:20:22,120 --> 00:20:24,560
you are attracted to both men and women.

320
00:20:24,600 --> 00:20:26,040
If you are an enby,

321
00:20:26,040 --> 00:20:29,480
you just don’t want to be judged
by your sexuality.

322
00:20:30,280 --> 00:20:31,600
Or you are pansexual?

323
00:20:32,040 --> 00:20:34,280
Or you are a lesbian but just realized it?

324
00:20:36,280 --> 00:20:38,280
I’ve never thought about it before.

325
00:20:38,320 --> 00:20:39,880
How should I define myself?

326
00:20:40,240 --> 00:20:41,280
That’s enough.

327
00:20:41,400 --> 00:20:43,280
Stop pressuring my girlfriend.

328
00:20:43,760 --> 00:20:46,440
Let her define who she is.

329
00:20:46,480 --> 00:20:47,960
Stop forcing her.

330
00:20:48,360 --> 00:20:50,040
As long as she’s happy with it.

331
00:20:50,960 --> 00:20:52,440
You’re so protective of her.

332
00:20:54,600 --> 00:20:58,360
No matter what you are,
Praew still loves you.

333
00:20:58,880 --> 00:21:01,400
She’s not the type
who falls in love easily.

334
00:21:01,720 --> 00:21:02,800
I’ll tell you something.

335
00:21:02,840 --> 00:21:05,760
You are her first girlfriend.

336
00:21:08,160 --> 00:21:09,760
That’s enough. Stop it.

337
00:21:10,080 --> 00:21:11,080
Will you stop?

338
00:21:12,080 --> 00:21:16,440
Everyone, let’s drink
to celebrate Min and Praew’s love.

339
00:21:18,320 --> 00:21:21,880
Min-Praew.

340
00:21:25,720 --> 00:21:26,760
Do you want a bite?

341
00:21:41,320 --> 00:21:42,080
Here.

342
00:21:42,480 --> 00:21:43,760
Drink some water.

343
00:21:43,800 --> 00:21:45,240
So you won’t get a hangover.

344
00:21:56,320 --> 00:21:58,280
Thank you for taking me
to meet your friends.

345
00:21:59,520 --> 00:22:01,880
I thought it would be awkward
talking to them.

346
00:22:02,240 --> 00:22:03,680
Because of our big age gap.

347
00:22:05,800 --> 00:22:07,560
I should be the one who thanks you.

348
00:22:08,480 --> 00:22:10,280
For stepping into my world.

349
00:22:13,280 --> 00:22:15,480
Of course, I want to come into your world.

350
00:22:16,720 --> 00:22:18,560
Meeting your friends.

351
00:22:19,640 --> 00:22:21,240
Learning new things about you.

352
00:22:24,360 --> 00:22:26,760
It makes me feel even more important
to you than I was before.

353
00:22:39,480 --> 00:22:41,280
You are important to me.

354
00:22:49,720 --> 00:22:52,360
At first, I couldn’t picture us together.

355
00:22:54,760 --> 00:22:57,240
I couldn’t picture
how I would be a part of your life

356
00:22:58,080 --> 00:23:00,400
and how you would be a part of my life.

357
00:23:04,400 --> 00:23:06,160
But I can see it clearly now.

358
00:23:10,440 --> 00:23:13,360
Please stay with me
so I can see it clearly like this.

359
00:23:19,960 --> 00:23:20,640
Yes.

360
00:23:46,560 --> 00:23:47,360
Prim.

361
00:23:48,200 --> 00:23:49,440
Did you see this?

362
00:23:49,560 --> 00:23:50,480
See what?

363
00:23:50,720 --> 00:23:51,640
This.

364
00:23:52,560 --> 00:23:53,360
What?

365
00:23:54,840 --> 00:23:57,720
You are nominated for best ad director.

366
00:23:59,080 --> 00:24:00,840
Really?

367
00:24:01,080 --> 00:24:03,760
Other nominees are all famous directors.

368
00:24:04,280 --> 00:24:06,480
I’m so happy for you. You made it.

369
00:24:12,240 --> 00:24:14,760
Did Min know this?

370
00:24:17,320 --> 00:24:18,360
I’m not sure.

371
00:24:18,600 --> 00:24:19,960
I haven’t seen her today.

372
00:24:26,160 --> 00:24:27,880
Are you two still not talking?

373
00:24:29,520 --> 00:24:31,160
She refuses to talk to me.

374
00:24:33,960 --> 00:24:35,880
You two are best friends.

375
00:24:36,760 --> 00:24:38,360
You built this company together.

376
00:24:39,120 --> 00:24:40,560
You are nominated

377
00:24:41,000 --> 00:24:42,480
because you two worked together.

378
00:24:47,520 --> 00:24:48,320
Come on.

379
00:24:48,760 --> 00:24:50,040
You should make up with her.

380
00:24:50,560 --> 00:24:51,880
Put down your ego.

381
00:24:58,000 --> 00:24:59,920
I’ll tell others about this. See you.

382
00:25:25,440 --> 00:25:26,360
I’m sorry.

383
00:25:26,960 --> 00:25:28,680
My mom gets too involved.

384
00:25:30,200 --> 00:25:31,360
You don’t have to apologize.

385
00:25:31,680 --> 00:25:32,560
I get it.

386
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:34,880
You also want to spend time with your mom.

387
00:25:35,800 --> 00:25:36,560
No.

388
00:25:36,840 --> 00:25:39,760
I don’t need her love that much.

389
00:25:40,720 --> 00:25:41,760
One more thing.

390
00:25:42,040 --> 00:25:43,880
I’ve been living alone for so long.

391
00:25:44,400 --> 00:25:45,960
I don’t feel like I’m missing anything.

392
00:25:46,400 --> 00:25:47,640
But I just don’t want to have problems.

393
00:25:47,760 --> 00:25:49,440
She is your mom.

394
00:25:50,960 --> 00:25:52,440
Anyone can be a mom.

395
00:25:52,520 --> 00:25:54,240
All they have to do is give birth to a child.

396
00:25:54,640 --> 00:25:55,760
Isn’t that too harsh?

397
00:25:57,800 --> 00:25:59,640
You might want to think it over.

398
00:26:00,440 --> 00:26:01,880
I don’t want to cause you a problem.

399
00:26:04,160 --> 00:26:06,680
I’ve never seen you as a problem.

400
00:26:07,960 --> 00:26:09,720
I’m now happy.

401
00:26:10,400 --> 00:26:11,560
It’s because of you.

402
00:26:14,240 --> 00:26:15,960
But family is still important.

403
00:26:16,360 --> 00:26:17,640
You should give it a try.

404
00:26:18,320 --> 00:26:20,040
Maybe your mom will understand you.

405
00:26:21,360 --> 00:26:25,360
Not everyone is longing for love
from their family.

406
00:26:25,640 --> 00:26:26,960
Sometimes, friends

407
00:26:30,880 --> 00:26:34,560
or a girlfriend can fill the void.

408
00:26:42,200 --> 00:26:43,480
Let’s go public with our relationship.

409
00:26:44,000 --> 00:26:44,760
What?

410
00:26:45,200 --> 00:26:46,280
Are you serious?

411
00:26:46,880 --> 00:26:48,560
Your mom will never let us do that.

412
00:26:50,680 --> 00:26:52,080
Did she tell you that?

413
00:27:01,480 --> 00:27:04,840
If you want to do it, she can’t stop us.

414
00:27:05,320 --> 00:27:07,240
I want people to know
about our relationship.

415
00:27:07,640 --> 00:27:11,640
But I’ll respect your decision.

416
00:27:14,960 --> 00:27:15,960
I want to do it.

417
00:27:16,320 --> 00:27:18,320
Why wouldn’t I want you to show me off?

418
00:27:28,200 --> 00:27:29,480
Let’s show it off, shall we?

419
00:27:33,600 --> 00:27:35,080
Are you ready to be a celebrity?

420
00:27:37,320 --> 00:27:39,280
I’m ready since the day
I agreed to be your girlfriend.

421
00:27:41,640 --> 00:27:42,640
Then I’ll post it.

422
00:27:59,680 --> 00:28:00,960
Hello.

423
00:28:09,080 --> 00:28:13,080
Sorry, I no longer manage Prim’s schedule.

424
00:28:15,480 --> 00:28:18,760
I’ll send her contact info to you.

425
00:28:20,240 --> 00:28:22,080
Can I send it to this number?

426
00:28:22,720 --> 00:28:23,560
Sure.

427
00:28:26,680 --> 00:28:28,160
Are you really leaving Prim?

428
00:28:29,640 --> 00:28:30,960
She left me first.

429
00:28:31,720 --> 00:28:33,560
Why don’t you talk things out with her?

430
00:28:33,960 --> 00:28:35,080
I tried,

431
00:28:35,760 --> 00:28:37,280
but it was useless.

432
00:28:37,720 --> 00:28:39,160
Whose side are you taking?

433
00:28:39,160 --> 00:28:40,680
You’re supposed to support me.

434
00:28:42,320 --> 00:28:44,040
I am supporting you.

435
00:28:44,280 --> 00:28:45,960
I’m supporting both of you.

436
00:28:46,640 --> 00:28:48,000
You are a feeling type.

437
00:28:48,040 --> 00:28:49,440
She is a thinking type.

438
00:28:49,680 --> 00:28:51,360
It’s up to you how you look at it.

439
00:28:52,280 --> 00:28:54,880
Right now, I need a girlfriend
who supports me,

440
00:28:55,560 --> 00:28:56,880
not a girlfriend who puts me down.

441
00:29:00,880 --> 00:29:03,240
Okay, I get it.

442
00:29:03,640 --> 00:29:05,560
If you want to vent
or have something to say,

443
00:29:05,600 --> 00:29:06,840
you can do it.

444
00:29:06,880 --> 00:29:08,160
I’m here to listen to you.

445
00:29:09,600 --> 00:29:12,840
Isn’t this what a girlfriend is for?
To listen to you venting about your friend.

446
00:29:15,200 --> 00:29:16,240
That’s right.

447
00:29:17,000 --> 00:29:22,880
All you need to do is nod
and agree with everything I say.

448
00:29:25,400 --> 00:29:26,160
Sure.

449
00:29:27,160 --> 00:29:29,560
Even though I disagree with you.

450
00:29:30,520 --> 00:29:31,960
I’ll say it later.

451
00:29:38,000 --> 00:29:38,680
Come on.

452
00:29:39,240 --> 00:29:40,280
I’m ready.

453
00:29:40,680 --> 00:29:43,960
You can vent out or complain
as much as you want.

454
00:29:44,000 --> 00:29:45,160
I’ll listen to you.

455
00:29:45,920 --> 00:29:49,520
You can start from the first day
that you opened the company together.

456
00:29:50,320 --> 00:29:51,360
I’m ready to listen to you.

457
00:29:54,040 --> 00:29:56,760
I won’t talk or complain about her.

458
00:29:58,000 --> 00:29:59,160
Let’s cuddle.

459
00:30:02,800 --> 00:30:03,560
Fine.

460
00:30:18,880 --> 00:30:20,040
Congratulations.

461
00:30:20,080 --> 00:30:21,120
You’ve been working for only a few years.

462
00:30:21,120 --> 00:30:22,760
But you’re already nominated
for a big award.

463
00:30:22,960 --> 00:30:24,640
It’s only a nomination.
I haven’t won it yet.

464
00:30:24,640 --> 00:30:25,960
Don’t get too excited.

465
00:30:26,320 --> 00:30:28,040
It’s already an amazing thing.

466
00:30:28,040 --> 00:30:29,520
You are the only woman among the nominees.

467
00:30:29,520 --> 00:30:32,360
My girlfriend is so talented.

468
00:30:33,160 --> 00:30:35,240
Don’t you have a reward for me?

469
00:30:37,960 --> 00:30:39,080
What do you want?

470
00:30:39,280 --> 00:30:40,440
I can give you everything.

471
00:30:41,200 --> 00:30:42,160
Everything?

472
00:30:42,880 --> 00:30:43,640
Yes.

473
00:30:48,800 --> 00:30:50,560
This is a bigger reward than the award.

474
00:30:52,840 --> 00:30:53,640
That’s all?

475
00:30:54,680 --> 00:30:56,160
How can you be happy so easily?

476
00:30:57,440 --> 00:30:59,360
If you want to give me more than this,
I don’t mind.

477
00:30:59,400 --> 00:31:00,440
I’ll be happy to take it.

478
00:31:07,520 --> 00:31:10,080
I know what I’m going to give you.

479
00:31:18,480 --> 00:31:19,960
Where are you taking me?

480
00:31:20,440 --> 00:31:23,520
Didn’t you say you were going
to take me out to celebrate my nomination?

481
00:31:24,760 --> 00:31:27,240
I’m taking you to meet someone important.

482
00:31:28,280 --> 00:31:29,240
Who?

483
00:31:30,880 --> 00:31:31,680
Hold on.

484
00:31:31,960 --> 00:31:33,480
You are helping me too much.

485
00:31:33,680 --> 00:31:35,480
You hired me
to work on your mom’s project.

486
00:31:35,680 --> 00:31:37,320
You introduced me to a film producer.

487
00:31:37,720 --> 00:31:40,080
These are on my bucket list.

488
00:31:41,040 --> 00:31:42,280
There’s one thing left.

489
00:31:42,760 --> 00:31:46,080
Introduce me to a guide
and travel around the world with me.

490
00:31:47,200 --> 00:31:49,840
This person is very important.

491
00:31:50,280 --> 00:31:52,000
I’m sure you want to talk to her.

492
00:31:53,720 --> 00:31:56,040
Is it the director of Lady Bird?

493
00:31:56,320 --> 00:31:57,080
Yes.

494
00:31:57,440 --> 00:31:58,440
Are you kidding me?

495
00:31:59,240 --> 00:32:00,160
Really?

496
00:32:07,840 --> 00:32:09,760
This is the director of Lady Bird.

497
00:32:13,840 --> 00:32:16,880
The person you should share
the success with is not me.

498
00:32:18,480 --> 00:32:19,440
It should be Min.

499
00:32:40,520 --> 00:32:42,360
Did Bambi force you to come?

500
00:32:43,760 --> 00:32:44,680
No.

501
00:32:45,680 --> 00:32:47,760
But she told me that you were crying

502
00:32:47,960 --> 00:32:49,680
and whining that
you couldn’t live without me.

503
00:32:49,960 --> 00:32:50,960
She overstated.

504
00:32:51,360 --> 00:32:53,080
I didn’t shed any tears.

505
00:32:53,880 --> 00:32:55,600
So it means you are doing fine?

506
00:32:56,760 --> 00:32:58,280
You don’t seem to need me.

507
00:33:00,200 --> 00:33:01,760
Doing fine, your ass?

508
00:33:03,120 --> 00:33:04,960
I haven’t given any answers
to the clients yet.

509
00:33:05,000 --> 00:33:06,560
My schedule is chaotic.

510
00:33:09,040 --> 00:33:11,160
When I contacted suppliers,
the quotations were so pricey.

511
00:33:11,880 --> 00:33:13,960
I’m not good
at negotiating prices like you.

512
00:33:15,280 --> 00:33:17,280
I don’t know how to pay taxes.

513
00:33:18,840 --> 00:33:20,160
Don’t leave it overdue.

514
00:33:20,320 --> 00:33:21,680
Otherwise, you will have to pay a fine.

515
00:33:22,280 --> 00:33:23,280
I know that.

516
00:33:29,480 --> 00:33:30,840
Now, I know

517
00:33:31,880 --> 00:33:33,680
how important you are to me.

518
00:33:36,600 --> 00:33:38,480
All this time, I…

519
00:33:41,800 --> 00:33:44,360
I overlooked the people around me.

520
00:33:46,960 --> 00:33:47,800
You know this.

521
00:33:49,480 --> 00:33:50,360
You…

522
00:33:51,200 --> 00:33:53,640
You are behind my success.

523
00:33:54,960 --> 00:33:57,200
Without you, I wouldn’t have gotten
where I am today.

524
00:34:04,480 --> 00:34:07,360
I still remember the first day
we talked about opening a company together.

525
00:34:12,000 --> 00:34:16,880
We were looked down on
by male directors and producers.

526
00:34:17,840 --> 00:34:19,679
They told us to get them coffee.

527
00:34:22,600 --> 00:34:25,840
That’s the reason
we wanted to open a company for women.

528
00:34:31,560 --> 00:34:32,760
And we did it.

529
00:34:34,520 --> 00:34:36,360
Today, I received a nomination.

530
00:34:36,719 --> 00:34:39,280
Your name should have been included.

531
00:34:40,840 --> 00:34:41,639
No.

532
00:34:41,960 --> 00:34:43,560
You can do it by yourself.

533
00:34:45,199 --> 00:34:46,040
No.

534
00:34:49,080 --> 00:34:51,239
No one can achieve success by themselves.

535
00:34:56,440 --> 00:34:58,280
If I didn’t have a friend like you,

536
00:35:00,400 --> 00:35:02,480
my life would have fallen apart
a long time ago.

537
00:35:18,760 --> 00:35:20,760
Now, I understand
your decision about Bambi.

538
00:35:24,680 --> 00:35:27,360
Now, I get why you don’t want to lose her.

539
00:35:30,240 --> 00:35:31,360
I’ll help you.

540
00:35:34,200 --> 00:35:36,960
I’ll help you balance your work
and your love life.

541
00:35:41,920 --> 00:35:43,360
I’m not crying.

542
00:35:44,880 --> 00:35:46,080
I’m having hay fever.

543
00:36:34,680 --> 00:36:35,320
Hello.

544
00:36:35,560 --> 00:36:38,960
Did you tell Shasha
to post her photos with you?

545
00:36:39,360 --> 00:36:41,880
I told you to keep it a secret.

546
00:36:43,240 --> 00:36:44,960
I’ve never told her to do that.

547
00:36:45,560 --> 00:36:46,720
She did that herself.

548
00:36:47,120 --> 00:36:49,360
Why didn’t you stop her?

549
00:36:50,160 --> 00:36:51,440
What kind of girlfriend are you?

550
00:36:51,480 --> 00:36:53,360
Don’t you worry about her future?

551
00:36:54,040 --> 00:36:56,160
You know how things are in this business.

552
00:36:57,360 --> 00:36:58,680
Or what?

553
00:36:59,280 --> 00:37:02,120
Do you want to be famous
or expand your network?

554
00:37:03,320 --> 00:37:05,080
I heard you have your clothing brand.

555
00:37:05,560 --> 00:37:08,480
If you date a model,
it will help your sales, right?

556
00:37:09,720 --> 00:37:11,280
Why are you looking down on me like this?

557
00:37:11,920 --> 00:37:13,960
I have never asked anything from Shasha.

558
00:37:14,320 --> 00:37:16,440
I can make a living on my own.

559
00:37:17,080 --> 00:37:19,120
I’ve never asked anyone for money.

560
00:37:20,360 --> 00:37:21,960
I also have never wanted to be famous.

561
00:37:24,520 --> 00:37:26,760
I’ll warn you again.

562
00:37:27,080 --> 00:37:29,120
Don’t let anything like this happen again.

563
00:37:29,440 --> 00:37:33,240
If you still want to be her girlfriend,
you need to think about her future.

564
00:37:33,640 --> 00:37:34,800
Now, it’s time to make money.

565
00:37:35,440 --> 00:37:38,040
Love is not as important as money.

566
00:37:54,520 --> 00:37:55,200
Mom.

567
00:37:57,000 --> 00:37:57,960
Are you busy?

568
00:37:58,120 --> 00:37:59,480
I want to talk to you.

569
00:38:00,080 --> 00:38:01,560
Is it important?

570
00:38:14,480 --> 00:38:15,360
I…

571
00:38:17,360 --> 00:38:19,200
I’m going back to New York.

572
00:38:24,720 --> 00:38:25,880
Are you sure?

573
00:38:32,000 --> 00:38:33,160
Maybe…

574
00:38:33,920 --> 00:38:38,840
I will be happy
when I live in a new place,

575
00:38:40,720 --> 00:38:44,160
a place where I can’t cause problems
for the people I love.

576
00:38:49,640 --> 00:38:50,400
Bambi.

577
00:38:53,720 --> 00:38:56,840
You need to stop feeling responsible
for other people’s feelings.

578
00:38:58,960 --> 00:39:01,880
It’s not your job to make them happy.

579
00:39:05,720 --> 00:39:07,040
Yes, Mom.

580
00:39:07,520 --> 00:39:09,080
This time I chose myself.

581
00:39:11,120 --> 00:39:13,160
I’ll live there permanently.

582
00:39:15,680 --> 00:39:19,480
If moving there makes you feel better,
then do it.

583
00:39:20,480 --> 00:39:21,760
I will support you.

584
00:39:23,000 --> 00:39:24,360
If you need anything, just tell me.

585
00:39:26,000 --> 00:39:28,160
But I want you to make this decision

586
00:39:29,760 --> 00:39:31,640
for yourself,

587
00:39:33,880 --> 00:39:35,760
not just to make others happy.

588
00:39:35,920 --> 00:39:37,040
Do you hear me?

589
00:40:10,680 --> 00:40:12,120
Bambi, I’m here.

590
00:40:12,160 --> 00:40:14,040
Sorry for being late.

591
00:40:14,480 --> 00:40:16,080
I hurried as much as I could.

592
00:40:16,320 --> 00:40:19,080
I wrapped up the shooting so
fast that everyone was surprised.

593
00:40:20,520 --> 00:40:21,520
It’s okay.

594
00:40:21,560 --> 00:40:23,360
I’m working while waiting for you.

595
00:40:23,680 --> 00:40:24,640
It’s not a big deal.

596
00:40:25,960 --> 00:40:27,080
What are we going to do today?

597
00:40:27,120 --> 00:40:28,760
Is there anything you want to eat?

598
00:40:29,200 --> 00:40:30,960
I want to eat Chinese food.

599
00:40:42,600 --> 00:40:43,840
You…

600
00:40:45,080 --> 00:40:46,240
What’s wrong?

601
00:40:46,280 --> 00:40:48,080
Why are you acting strange?

602
00:40:49,920 --> 00:40:50,960
Don’t tell me

603
00:40:51,920 --> 00:40:56,680
you prepared a surprise for me,
like when you took me to see Min?

604
00:41:01,600 --> 00:41:02,360
I…

605
00:41:05,320 --> 00:41:06,920
I have something to tell you.

606
00:41:10,360 --> 00:41:12,440
I want to tell you in person.

607
00:41:15,320 --> 00:41:16,200
Tell me about what?

608
00:41:25,280 --> 00:41:26,680
I’m going to New York.

609
00:41:28,760 --> 00:41:30,160
Are you going there for work?

610
00:41:30,320 --> 00:41:31,480
When?

611
00:41:32,160 --> 00:41:34,280
Can I go with you?
I want to visit the city.

612
00:41:34,480 --> 00:41:37,080
But I need to work out my schedule
with Min first.

613
00:41:37,120 --> 00:41:39,160
Otherwise, she will kill me.

614
00:41:42,880 --> 00:41:43,880
No.

615
00:41:49,560 --> 00:41:50,480
I…

616
00:41:51,840 --> 00:41:53,880
I’m going to New York

617
00:41:58,120 --> 00:41:59,440
to live there permanently.

618
00:42:06,320 --> 00:42:07,480
What do you mean?

619
00:42:09,760 --> 00:42:11,080
I just…

620
00:42:11,520 --> 00:42:13,360
I don’t want to be your burden anymore.

621
00:42:15,840 --> 00:42:19,360
I don’t want you to choose
between me and your work.

622
00:42:20,240 --> 00:42:24,200
I don’t want you
to choose me over other things.

623
00:42:24,200 --> 00:42:25,440
I don’t want that.

624
00:42:25,480 --> 00:42:29,000
Bambi, everything has worked out.

625
00:42:29,000 --> 00:42:30,840
What are you worried about?

626
00:42:30,960 --> 00:42:32,880
There’s nothing to worry about anymore.

627
00:42:33,840 --> 00:42:35,080
I know.

628
00:42:38,520 --> 00:42:40,080
But it will happen again.

629
00:42:41,640 --> 00:42:43,480
It will happen again.

630
00:42:43,680 --> 00:42:45,680
It will keep happening.

631
00:42:45,880 --> 00:42:46,760
No, no.

632
00:42:46,960 --> 00:42:49,280
No, it won’t happen again.

633
00:42:49,480 --> 00:42:51,240
Because we are now more mature.

634
00:42:52,080 --> 00:42:54,040
We learned from our mistakes.

635
00:42:55,680 --> 00:42:57,240
I also learned…

636
00:42:59,640 --> 00:43:01,360
it’s useless for us to keep trying.

637
00:43:04,120 --> 00:43:06,760
You almost lost your best friend
because of me.

638
00:43:07,680 --> 00:43:08,760
I don’t know…

639
00:43:09,720 --> 00:43:12,000
what I will expect from you.

640
00:43:12,040 --> 00:43:13,080
I don’t know

641
00:43:13,120 --> 00:43:14,960
what I’m going to demand from you.

642
00:43:16,840 --> 00:43:18,520
I don’t want to feel this way again.

643
00:43:22,200 --> 00:43:24,120
If you want something, just tell me.

644
00:43:25,440 --> 00:43:27,520
I can move to New York with you.

645
00:43:27,560 --> 00:43:29,560
I want to go study there anyway.

646
00:43:30,720 --> 00:43:32,240
I can shoot a movie there.

647
00:43:38,520 --> 00:43:39,880
If you’re going to go there,

648
00:43:41,440 --> 00:43:42,960
you should go for your own goals,

649
00:43:45,000 --> 00:43:46,160
not for me.

650
00:43:50,960 --> 00:43:54,760
What about the bucket list
you promised to do with me?

651
00:43:59,520 --> 00:44:01,680
Aren’t you going to do
the last wish together?

652
00:44:07,240 --> 00:44:12,840
What if I stay and ruin
your first four wishes on the list?

653
00:44:17,920 --> 00:44:19,560
We have to accept

654
00:44:22,960 --> 00:44:24,680
that we were never meant to work out.

655
00:44:27,480 --> 00:44:29,360
We have to admit that we have to choose.

656
00:44:31,800 --> 00:44:33,560
But I chose you.

657
00:44:41,280 --> 00:44:42,560
But I chose myself.

658
00:44:45,480 --> 00:44:47,040
No, Bambi.

659
00:44:49,080 --> 00:44:51,840
Bambi, you overthink it.

660
00:44:54,720 --> 00:44:56,040
Don’t worry.

661
00:44:56,080 --> 00:44:58,280
There’s nothing to worry about.

662
00:44:59,000 --> 00:45:00,240
No, no.

663
00:45:00,400 --> 00:45:01,360
You should leave.

664
00:45:01,520 --> 00:45:03,360
-No.
-You should leave.

665
00:45:03,640 --> 00:45:05,640
No, please.

666
00:45:06,840 --> 00:45:08,680
Don’t do this.

667
00:45:11,440 --> 00:45:14,040
Bambi, don’t do this.

668
00:45:15,320 --> 00:45:16,160
You should leave.

669
00:45:16,280 --> 00:45:22,160
You know how miserable
my life is without you.

670
00:45:22,840 --> 00:45:26,040
Please leave. I want to be alone.

671
00:45:29,880 --> 00:45:30,560
Prim.

672
00:45:32,640 --> 00:45:33,480
Please.

673
00:46:27,080 --> 00:46:29,360
Don’t let love ruin your dream.

674
00:46:31,560 --> 00:46:34,040
When I decided to go public
with our relationship,

675
00:46:34,200 --> 00:46:36,160
I just wanted to have
a simple life with you.

676
00:46:36,920 --> 00:46:38,160
I want to kiss you when I want.

677
00:46:38,400 --> 00:46:42,840
Thank you for being an amazing girlfriend
and always supporting me.

678
00:46:43,560 --> 00:46:46,960
The next award is Best Newcomer Director.

679
00:46:50,360 --> 00:46:53,080
I have a new wish on my bucket list.
